Findings

To summarize: - Closed Date correlates (weak negative -0.314839425) with Extensions per Loan;
- More loans will delay closed dates, which seems obvious;
- the same status get Extensions per loan with Loan Closed Date -0.314839425;
- The signed dated and closed date shows the weak positive correlation;
- Delay Days and Closed Date -0.3793944729 weak negative correlation;
- Number_Of additional agreements have a strong positive correlation with Additional.Amount_SUM, after each new agreement chance that sum will grow - also seems quite obvious
- Amount_SUM strong correlation with the first date where customer take an additional loan;
- Number_OF_AA created_1 - 0.740886542;
- the rest of attr. doesn’t provide info about significant or moderate corrlation.
